Nat's 5 LAME st records

Even maybe more essential the avoid list of five records that I bought and that I think you should be prejudiced against:

Joe Satriani self titled.

Man, this is the guy who "surfed with the alien". Now he's balding (or why the many "hat-pics") and he's got the blues. Alright Joe lose some more hair, maybe you'll get the blues for real. Sucks worse than my Hoover 1400. (Also avoid the Extremist, at full price at least)

Die Krupps - Final Option

Die Krupps is a band of poseurs, playing a mindless and feeble sounding mixture of electronic music and metal. Sounds awful.

Skrew - Dusted

You might have heard this is just like Ministry ? Well like very boring Ministry. Avoid ! Avoid!
Dream Theater - When Dream and Day Unite

DT is totally hyped by the media. This may be very nice technically, but music-wise it's 2/3 GB of valium.

Praxis- Metatron

This is unlistenable in my opinion. The previous record "Mutans Mutandis" (?) had some really good moments in the middle of unlistenableness. This doesn't. Sometimes I put this on to test, whether my music taste has evolved enough to understand this record... not the last 5 years or so, it hasn't.

Nat! (nat@zumdick.rhein-main.de)
